Access Protection (Access Modifiers)

Access modifiers control visibility of classes, methods, and variables across packages.

Modifier	Within Class	Same Package	Subclass (Other Package)	Other Packages
private	âœ…	âŒ	âŒ	âŒ
default (no modifier)	âœ…	âœ…	âŒ	âŒ
protected	âœ…	âœ…	âœ…	âŒ
public	âœ…	âœ…	âœ…	âœ…
ğŸ”¹ Example of Access Control
package school;

public class Student {
    public int rollNo = 1;
    private String name = "Riya";
    protected String course = "Java";
    int age = 20; // default
}

package test;
import school.Student;

public class AccessDemo extends Student {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        AccessDemo obj = new AccessDemo();
        System.out.println(obj.rollNo);    // accessible (public)
        System.out.println(obj.course);    // accessible (protected)
        // System.out.println(obj.name);   // not accessible (private)
        // System.out.println(obj.age);    // not accessible (default)
    }
}
